/* kernel/memaccess_c
* SYNOPSIS
* to be added 
* short introduction of the kernel 
* and of the persons concerned with the kernel
* SEE ALSO
* if you want to referenz anything else - here is your chance
* DESCRIPTION
* -----------------------------------------------------------
* Content
* 1) What the kernel does
* 2) What can I change ?
* 3) Hints
* -----------------------------------------------------------
* 
* 1) The kernel measures the average time of a single
*    memory access depending on the accessed memory size.
*    It does something like: 
*      for loop = ...
*      {
*        var = memory{random_field];
*      }
*    Typically you will see (on scalar processors) the 
*    latencies of the several cache hierarchies.
*      
*    The x axis shows the memory area used for a run.
*    The y axis shows the average memory access time.
* 
* -----------------------------------------------------------
* 
* 2) Edit PARAMETERS to change the used memory sizes.
* 
* -----------------------------------------------------------
* 
* 3) Mulitply the y axis with the processor clock to
*    obtain the results in processor cycles.
* 
* -----------------------------------------------------------
*
***
*/
